Package: tcgar
Title: A small helper package for using The Cancer Genome Atlas (TCGA) data
Version: 0.0.3
Authors@R: person("Christian", "Diener", email = "mail@cdiener.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: tcgar helps you to obtain and parse TCGA data for use in analysis
    pipelines such as the ones in bioconductor. In comparison to other packages
    tcgar aims to help you to download a lot of data at once and to read it fast.
    For instance you can download all the data for a given technology with
    two lines of code and reading it will take only a few minutes at most.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.2)
Imports:
    data.table, stringr, RCurl
License: MIT + file LICENSE
LazyData: true
Suggests:
    testthat
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
